{{Uniform hyperbolic tiles db|Uniform hyperbolic tiling stat table|U55_s}}
In [[geometry]], the '''snub pentapentagonal tiling''' is a uniform tiling of the [[Hyperbolic geometry|hyperbolic plane]]. It has [[Schläfli symbol]] of sr{5,5}, constructed from two regular pentagons and three equilateral triangles around every vertex.

== Images ==
Drawn in chiral pairs, with edges missing between black triangles:
:[[File:H2 snub 255a.png|240px]][[File:H2 snub 255b.png|240px]]

== Symmetry==
A double [[Uniform coloring|symmetry coloring]] can be constructed from [5,4] symmetry with only one color pentagon. It has [[Schläfli symbol]] s{5,4}, and [[Coxeter diagram]] {{CDD|node_h|5|node_h|4|node}}.
:[[File:Uniform tiling 542-h01.png|240px]]

