In [[geometry]], the '''trioctagonal tiling''' is a semiregular tiling of the hyperbolic plane, representing a [[Rectification (geometry)|rectified]] [[Order-3 octagonal tiling]]. There are two [[triangle]]s and two [[octagon]]s alternating on each [[vertex (geometry)|vertex]]. It has [[Schläfli symbol]] of ''r''{8,3}.

